==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxanilamide
<hw>Ox`a*nil*am"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Oxanil</ets>ic + <ets>amide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white crystalline nitrogenous substance, obtained indirectly by
the action of cyanogen on aniline, and regarded as an anilide of oxamic
acid; -- called also <altname>phenyl oxamide</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxanilate</ent>⟦br⟧
